00:00:10,990 --> 00:00:14,025
How would you respond if I asked you,

2
00:00:14,025 --> 00:00:16,815
"Do you know how long it'll take me to get to the bank?"

3
00:00:16,815 --> 00:00:19,060
You'd probably ask, "Where are you?"

4
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:20,420
"Where's the bank?"

5
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:23,270
"Are you walking, driving, biking?"

6
00:00:23,270 --> 00:00:27,241
But if you just guess the details of my situation to direct me to the bank,

7
00:00:27,241 --> 00:00:30,785
your response would be a day late and a dollar short.

8
00:00:30,785 --> 00:00:33,335
It seems like such a natural thing to ask questions

9
00:00:33,335 --> 00:00:35,984
and gather information to solve a problem,

10
00:00:35,984 --> 00:00:39,300
but it's usually one of those most overlooked steps in troubleshooting.

11
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:43,780
Troubleshooting is the ability to diagnose and resolve a problem.

12
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:48,350
One of the most difficult skills to acquire in an IT role isn't technical knowledge,

13
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:54,200
but effective troubleshooting, whether that's helping someone face-to-face or remotely.

14
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,490
It's not specific to the IT world either.

15
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:59,270
We use troubleshooting skills every day.

16
00:00:59,270 --> 00:01:00,610
My car is broken.

17
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:03,270
The light bulb went out. I feel sick.

18
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:05,495
Imagine if you went to your doctor and said,

19
00:01:05,495 --> 00:01:08,810
"I feel sick," and without any other information,

20
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:11,295
he gives you a prescription for allergy medicine.

21
00:01:11,295 --> 00:01:12,710
Time to find a new doctor.

22
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:14,700
While this might seem far-fetched,

23
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,380
this can happen pretty often in the IT world.

24
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,270
We're so in the habit of fixing things that sometimes,

25
00:01:20,270 --> 00:01:23,540
we try to fix something without diagnosing it first.

26
00:01:23,540 --> 00:01:27,065
We're going to give you the tools you need to develop good troubleshooting habits.

27
00:01:27,065 --> 00:01:29,765
No matter how big or small the problem is,

28
00:01:29,765 --> 00:01:34,160
the first thing to do in troubleshooting is ask questions.

29
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:36,740
There are a lot of factors that can cause a problem.

30
00:01:36,740 --> 00:01:41,105
You want to make sure you gather all your data before you start to tinker with it.

31
