these different scenarios would play out in real world settings.

43
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:11,420
Let's look at a quick scenario of a not-so-awesome troubleshooting interaction,

44
00:02:11,420 --> 00:02:15,515
and an awesome one.

45
00:02:15,515 --> 00:02:18,060
My computer is broken.

46
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:22,410
Oh, this looks bad.

47
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:24,535
I think you're going to need a new computer.

48
00:02:24,535 --> 00:02:27,840
It's going to be about a 1000 bucks.

49
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:31,600
My computer is broken.

50
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:35,305
Oh, okay.

51
00:02:35,305 --> 00:02:38,455
Can you tell me a little bit more about how it's broken?

52
00:02:38,455 --> 00:02:40,056
Does it turn on at all?

53
00:02:40,056 --> 00:02:42,730
Has there been any damage to it lately that you know of?

54
00:02:42,730 --> 00:02:45,195
Well, when I hit the power button,

55
00:02:45,195 --> 00:02:48,270
I hear a "ding," but nothing comes up on screen.

56
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:50,600
Oh, okay. Can I take a look?

57
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,688
Sure.

58
00:02:51,688 --> 00:02:52,700
Okay.

59
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:58,005
Let me just see what's going on here.

60
00:02:58,005 --> 00:03:01,350
You know what?

61
